"Thus both aluminum and iron coagulants are more polar than water. It is "
"possible that their strong polarity enables them to displace the water that "
"is bound to particles' surfaces and then form bonds with those surfaces. In "
"order to displace water molecules that are bound to the particles surfaces, "
"the coagulants must have stronger bonds to particles surfaces than the polar "
